>What is this?

Era games are a group of (usually) Japanese-developed text porn games.
They're not exclusively related to the Touhou franchise, but it's one of the series with most era games.

>Games usually discussed here
eraTohoTW - Comfy Touhou dating simulator with timestop shenanigans.
eraTohoK - Tactical game about conquering Gensokyo through any (absolutely any) means.
eraMegaten - Dungeon crawler based on the Shin Megami Tensei series, with tons of characters from other series (Fate, Touhou, Madoka, etc) included.

>Links
- WIKI: https://wiki.eragames.rip/index.php/Main_Page
Guides and downloads for all era games. For TW you should get the eng-development version, eng-release is several years old.
- GIT: https://gitgud.io/era-games
Git repository that has latest official builds to any of the games, you can sometimes find more recent versions than the ones on the wiki.
- AUTO UPDATER: http://madhammer.club/files/era-updater.7z
Fetches the latest version of TW, K or Megaten from the official git, no login needed.
- TW NEODEV: https://gitgud.io/Pedy/pedy-tw/-/releases
Git repository with a version of TW that gets more frequent updates. Might introduce more bugs, though they usually get fixed on the following release.
- JAP WIKI: https://seesaawiki.jp/eraseries/
- TRANSLATOR: https://wiki.eragames.rip/index.php/Sugoi
Automatic translator which copies text straight from the game. Comes with an optional customized built-in offline model.
You can also download the latest version at:
https://drive.google.com/file/d/1DA8voYO62ARtORzxJUBhMWK2FWbt6Vlq/view
- BUGS?: https://wiki.eragames.rip/bugreport.php
Report them over here.

>How to play?
Run anchor.exe, japanese locale is advised so you don't run into untranslated text.
If you wish to manually update, delete old files aside the sav and dat folders to avoid any bugs.

>How can I help?
Read https://wiki.eragames.rip/index.php/Contributing for starters.
You could try your hand at translating dialogue, there are guides currently in the TW folder (in #Translation) on what to do, not sure if it that folder exists in other games.
Another guide is:
1) Download an IDE. VS Code, for example.
1a) If using VS Code, install the EraBasic addon
2) Select UTF8 encoding
3) Open the ERB files and edit them
That way you can now edit files without much trouble.
The path for files to edit is usually the ERB folder:
K: ERB/口上
TW: ERB\口上・メッセージ関連\個人口上

You can also report bugs or typos here on the thread when you see them.
If you'd like to either edit or add your own portraits, the files are located within the 'resources' folder in webp format. You can use paint.net to edit them

This reminds me of a story from the Allied Occupation.

During the war, Japanese newspapers were heavily censored, and so before the paper went to print, someone from the government would put literal pieces of paper over the proof to show what had to be taken out. The newspapers just blanked out that part of the proof and replaced it with the word "CENSORED".

The Allies come in, and of course demand their own censorship of Japanese newspapers. So the newspapers run their proofs past the allies, get the censorship instructions, and then print it the same way, with the word "CENSORED" over huge parts of the paper. The Allies get furious, and call in the newspaper editors, explaining to them that they didn't want readers to KNOW that the content was being censored.

"So what do we call it, then?" said the editors.
"I don't know," said the Allied GHQ guy; "say something like that you 'voluntarily restrained from publishing it', if anyone asks".

The next day, newspapers came out in Tokyo with massive areas blanked out, replaced by the large word "VOLUNTARILY RESTRAINED".

To this day, "voluntary restraint", or 自主規制 in Japanese, is used to describe some form of censorship or restriction that isn't officially acknowledged but that everyone knows exists.

With a small smile on her face she said simply, "no its fine... let me help you actually.." still trying to get up you stopped for a second you looked up at her confused. It was then that in that split second you turned your head up she was already standing and with one or two steps lifted you by the collar of your shirt, now face to face you could see that smile was cold as ice and it honestly scared you more then when she was boiling in rage. I know you haven't been happy with me but don't you think faking a fall like that was a bit much Anon?". She nodded, and said in a voice that left no room for debate, "I suppose you'd want me to believe that..." suddenly the grip on the bottle changed with speed you wouldn't have believed before coming from Gensokyo and rage finally flaring in her eyes the bottle that was now in a grip like a club would be came crashing down on your head. The bottle collided on the top of your head, with the middle of the bottle being the contact point and despite it still having some contents the bottle shattered against you and your vision went red with pain then black for a second.

Needless to say it flared up again in pain as you were cast to the floor giving a small shout of pain as you impacted the tatami with your knee and before you could do anything the sadistic miko was on you again using her purification rod liberally.
